Defendant Lindsay M Mathson in court with attorney Joseph Smith.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Attorney Gordon puts an oral read in on the record.  Cases 15CM1914 and 15CM888 are dismissed and read in as well.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Smith makes statements.  State has complied with the victim rights notification.  Defendant's father makes statements. Defendant makes statements. 
The Court Orders the Following:  Count #1.  
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
12 months without work release
Term of Probation: 3 Years
Early release after 2 years if deemed by agent.  
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician this case and probation conditions. 
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Seek employment or school;
Participate with the Day Report Center for 90 days after the defendants release from the Waukesha County Jail. 
FINE or COSTS:  $268.00  to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $250.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
